      "correctOption": 0,
      "correctAnswer": null,
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "subject": "Chemistry",
      "topic": "chemical-reactions-for-aldehydes-and-ketones",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "<p>$$ \\mathrm{x}=\\mathrm{H}_2(\\text { gas }), \\mathrm{y}=\\mathrm{CO}_2(\\text { gas }) $$</p>\n<p>Now find the molar mass of each gas:</p>\n<p>The molar mass of $\\mathrm{H}_2$ is $2\\ \\text{g mol}^{-1}$.</p>\n<p>The molar mass of $\\mathrm{CO}_2$ is $12+16\\times 2=44\\ \\text{g mol}^{-1}$.</p>\n<p>Sum of molar mass $=2+44=46$</p>",
